Package: axon
Version: 1.0.0
Section: net
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: iptables (>= 1.8), iproute2 (>= 5.0), libnetfilter-queue1
Recommends: clang, llvm, linux-headers-generic
Installed-Size: 8192
Maintainer: axon <axon@localhost>
Description: Hybrid L3/L7 Per-Interface FQDN Firewall
 A high-performance firewall combining eBPF/XDP for L3 packet filtering
 with an L7 inspection engine for shared-IP FQDN-based blocking.
 .
 Features:
  - Per-interface XDP programs for L3 filtering
  - FQDN-centric rules with TTL-aware DNS resolution
  - DNS grace periods prevent false drops on IP changes
  - L7 inspection via NFQUEUE for TLS SNI and HTTP Host
  - Cold start recovery from persistent bbolt storage
  - gRPC control plane with CLI
  - Fan-out Protobuf logging via TCP (default: localhost:5000)
  - allow-all / block-all modes per interface
Homepage: https://github.com/axon/axon
